This paper is about large-scale direct numerical simulations of fluid turbulence using a highly parallel fast multipole method on GPUs. It involves numerical methods and high-performance computing, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which covers numerical methods and simulations in various fields, including fluid dynamics. The second likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which covers high-performance computing and parallel algorithms. The third likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which covers numerical methods and algorithms for solving mathematical problems. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software), which covers software and algorithms for mathematical computations. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Algebraic Manipulation), which covers symbolic and algebraic methods for solving mathematical problems.
